1
00:00:35,159 --> 00:00:37,000
I spent a peaceful and fulfilling week.

2
00:00:41,119 --> 00:00:43,719
I even applied to my department for early exams.

3
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:45,240
Hoping

4
00:00:45,799 --> 00:00:47,320
I can still get my grades for this semester.

5
00:00:49,039 --> 00:00:49,439
Xu Rui.

6
00:00:49,759 --> 00:00:50,200
Look.

7
00:00:51,079 --> 00:00:52,600
This book was actually written by Professor Zhuang.

8
00:00:54,159 --> 00:00:55,200
Hurry up and review properly.

9
00:00:56,799 --> 00:00:57,200
Go.

10
00:01:09,159 --> 00:01:10,280
My mom has been very calm too.

11
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:11,560
It seems like

12
00:01:11,879 --> 00:01:13,400
after chatting with Professor Zhuang,

13
00:01:14,439 --> 00:01:15,719
she turned back into the

14
00:01:16,239 --> 00:01:17,680
Kong Guifang I'm familiar with.

15
00:01:19,439 --> 00:01:20,760
Or maybe we both know

16
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:22,599
what we are waiting for.

17
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:51,480
Little Daxue's parents told us

18
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:52,959
that a week ago,

19
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:54,799
they signed the organ donation agreement.

20
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:56,799
Unexpectedly,

21
00:01:57,719 --> 00:01:58,640
my mom signed it too.

22
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:01,519
This is a thank-you letter from our foundation.

23
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:02,480
And the registration certificate.

24
00:02:05,159 --> 00:02:06,319
They also gave this.

25
00:02:06,719 --> 00:02:07,640
As a keepsake for me.

26
00:02:08,039 --> 00:02:10,199
Please carry that card with you.

27
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:11,800
If anything unexpected happens,

28
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:14,000
you'll save my organs immediately.

29
00:02:16,759 --> 00:02:17,199
Xiaocan.

30
00:02:18,159 --> 00:02:18,919
Are you donating?

31
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:26,639
Let me think about it.

32
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:00,240
Look at the oranges.

33
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,280
The oranges are excellent.

34
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:02,960
Boss, your oranges

35
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:04,319
are more expensive than other places.

36
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,520
How can they be the same?

37
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:06,759
These are Gannan navel oranges.

38
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:07,560
Actually,

39
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,560
I kind of want to donate too.

40
00:03:09,639 --> 00:03:11,080
From Jiangxi, the authentic taste of Jiangxi.

41
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,000
To be able to live on in another way.

42
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:15,520
That phrase is very tempting.

43
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,919
I just can't figure out

44
00:03:19,599 --> 00:03:21,439
if my mom has truly let go,

45
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:23,360
or if she's scheming something again.

46
00:03:24,599 --> 00:03:25,840
I'm afraid that once I'm gone,

47
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,800
and I have to donate my organs,

48
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:29,719
she wouldn't be able to take it.

49
00:03:29,879 --> 00:03:31,439
Look at this, this is great.

50
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,919
Little Daxue and his parents

51
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,000
are really amazing.

52
00:03:53,319 --> 00:03:54,080
Mom, this isn't working.

53
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,599
Just taking pills isn't bringing the fever down.

54
00:03:56,479 --> 00:03:57,759
Come on, let's go to the hospital.

55
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:58,479
No way.

56
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,479
I'm fine, I already took the fever medicine.

57
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:02,560
I'll be fine after a nap.

58
00:04:03,599 --> 00:04:05,400
Let's talk about everything else tomorrow.

59
00:04:06,159 --> 00:04:06,719
One last time.

60
00:04:07,159 --> 00:04:08,000
You sleep a bit more now.

61
00:04:08,319 --> 00:04:09,360
I'll come check in half an hour.

62
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:10,360
If your fever still hasn't gone down,

63
00:04:10,759 --> 00:04:12,199
I'll drag you to the hospital if I have to.

64
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:16,839
Hey.

65
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:18,000
Be good.

66
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:20,480
Go to sleep early.

67
00:05:58,519 --> 00:05:59,120
Xiaocan.

68
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,000
Xiaocan.

69
00:06:12,439 --> 00:06:13,360
Xiaocan.

70
00:07:05,199 --> 00:07:06,519
Mom, feeling any better?

71
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:08,120
That cold medicine and the fever...

72
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:18,360
What's the fuss about now?

73
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,160
Calm down.

74
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:20,160
Calm down.

75
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:21,160
Why?

76
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,240
What gives you the right to break the contract?

77
00:07:22,519 --> 00:07:23,480
Break what contract?

78
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:24,279
Nonsense.

79
00:07:24,279 --> 00:07:25,240
What are you talking about?

80
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,839
You're arguing with me now?

81
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:39,560
So what?

82
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:42,680
So what?

83
00:07:44,399 --> 00:07:45,319
I'll throw you out too.

84
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,720
Just destroy it all.

85
00:07:48,079 --> 00:07:48,959
Run then. Run.

86
00:07:49,399 --> 00:07:50,839
Run. Fine.

87
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:53,920
Why do we noble aliens...

88
00:07:54,439 --> 00:07:55,959
...always fall into the hands of you humans?

89
00:07:56,079 --> 00:07:57,160
Don't play dumb with me.

90
00:07:58,480 --> 00:07:59,040
Let me ask you.

91
00:07:59,639 --> 00:08:01,480
Is my mom aging because of your tricks?

92
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,199
How could I play tricks?

93
00:08:04,439 --> 00:08:05,279
On the entire Earth...

94
00:08:05,279 --> 00:08:07,360
...the one we fear provoking the most is your mom.

95
00:08:08,959 --> 00:08:11,040
The total Life Energy of you and your mom...

96
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:12,879
...hasn't changed at all.

97
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:13,839
Unless...

98
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:16,680
Speak.

99
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:22,639
The current Life Energy...

100
00:08:22,639 --> 00:08:23,839
...does not change.

101
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:26,319
It's migrated from future energy.

102
00:08:26,839 --> 00:08:28,000
If the future collapses...

103
00:08:28,319 --> 00:08:29,120
...then the energy is gone.

104
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,160
And it will affect the present.

105
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,960
Which means it's possible...

106
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,120
Speak human.

107
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:39,639
Your mom wants to kill herself.

108
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,600
If she has that thought...

109
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,080
...then her future disappears.

110
00:08:48,559 --> 00:08:50,480
Her thoughts will alter her present.

111
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:52,480
And her appearance will change too.

112
00:08:53,159 --> 00:08:55,440
We can't control her current thoughts.

113
00:09:03,559 --> 00:09:03,919
Then...

114
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:06,080
Do something!

115
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:06,559
You figure it out.

116
00:09:06,559 --> 00:09:07,039
Don't you have plenty of ways?

117
00:09:07,039 --> 00:09:07,919
What can we do?

118
00:09:07,919 --> 00:09:08,600
What can you do?

119
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,559
Is there a way?

120
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:10,759
Can't you erase memory?

121
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:12,320
Erase it! Erase her memory!

122
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,200
Erase memory...

123
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,080
If we erase her memory...

124
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,799
...you'll have to sign a supplemental agreement.

125
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,919
And there's a small price to pay.

126
00:09:19,919 --> 00:09:20,559
Speak.

127
00:09:21,759 --> 00:09:22,600
She will forget...

128
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:26,120
...everyone and everything related to this deal.

129
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:28,960
Including me?

130
00:09:30,639 --> 00:09:31,159
Yes.

131
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,240
But not necessarily.

132
00:09:33,279 --> 00:09:34,639
You've been together for too long.

133
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,759
If someone mentions you in front of her...

134
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:39,879
...she might still recover that memory.

135
00:09:40,559 --> 00:09:42,519
If you don't want her to remember this deal...

136
00:09:43,039 --> 00:09:44,879
...try not to appear around her.

137
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:47,120
And definitely don't call her Mom.

138
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:54,440
Do you agree?

139
00:10:09,519 --> 00:10:10,879
Xiaocan, are you okay?

140
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:16,519
I don't have a mom anymore.

141
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:21,679
I don't have a mom anymore, Xu Rui.

142
00:10:22,919 --> 00:10:23,600
It's okay.

143
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:24,960
I'm here.

144
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,120
You did a great job.

145
00:10:27,679 --> 00:10:28,159
Look.

146
00:10:28,799 --> 00:10:30,039
You protected Auntie.

147
00:10:30,799 --> 00:10:31,600
At least...

148
00:10:31,919 --> 00:10:34,240
Auntie won't break down because you're gone.

149
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:34,679
Right?

150
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:37,000
There, there. Stop crying.

151
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:43,720
What price did you pay again this time?

152
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:46,440
How much Life Energy did that profiteer take from you?

153
00:10:47,399 --> 00:10:48,279
It was okay this time.

154
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,799
He said it was free this time.

155
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:53,080
Anyway, I just signed a supplemental agreement.

156
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:59,399
Now, in my mom's memory...

157
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:01,320
I don't exist anymore.

158
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:05,120
Everything about me has become quite blurry.

159
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:06,559
She just thinks...

160
00:11:06,559 --> 00:11:08,200
She is the young Kong Guifang.

161
00:11:08,559 --> 00:11:09,960
Whenever I appear...

162
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:11,559
She might remember.

163
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,960
So I'd better try not to show up in the future.

164
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,320
To stop her from remembering.

165
00:11:20,559 --> 00:11:21,600
No wonder it was free.

166
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,759
This agreement is full of loopholes.

167
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:24,840
First of all...

168
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:27,360
They can't guarantee Auntie will never remember.

169
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,279
Which means...

170
00:11:28,639 --> 00:11:29,639
There are actually many ways...

171
00:11:29,639 --> 00:11:30,799
To make Auntie remember again.

172
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:32,960
This is a problem they caused in the first place.

173
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,279
They're probably just afraid you'll hold them accountable.

174
00:11:34,679 --> 00:11:35,519
Did you actually read it?

175
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,360
No.

176
00:11:38,639 --> 00:11:39,399
You didn't read it last time either.

177
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:40,320
And you still didn't read it now.

178
00:11:40,919 --> 00:11:42,919
The situation is always too urgent.

179
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:43,360
Just...

180
00:11:44,519 --> 00:11:45,000
Forget it.

181
00:11:45,879 --> 00:11:46,600
Let's just leave it at that.

182
00:11:47,519 --> 00:11:48,840
This might be the best outcome.

183
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:56,559
What's wrong?

184
00:11:56,879 --> 00:11:58,440
I didn't pack my stuff; it's all at home.

185
00:11:58,440 --> 00:11:59,519
My mom will be totally confused if she sees it.

186
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:02,840
Let's go!

187
00:12:09,399 --> 00:12:10,559
Thirty-eight point five.

188
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:12,879
Why won't it go down?

189
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:30,759
Why are there men's things here?

190
00:12:32,039 --> 00:12:33,240
I'm clearly single.

191
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,759
Am I not single?

192
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:41,879
How could I not remember a single man?

193
00:12:43,399 --> 00:12:44,919
Did the fever make me stupid?

194
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:57,399
Did I...

195
00:12:57,919 --> 00:12:58,720
move in with someone?

196
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:00,919
Guifang.

197
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,120
Long time no see.

198
00:13:02,799 --> 00:13:03,519
I'm here to mooch a meal.

199
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:12,240
Guifang.

200
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:14,159
Your condition at the hospital...

201
00:13:14,759 --> 00:13:15,759
Made me very worried.

202
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:17,360
I came to see you.

203
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,120
Actually...

204
00:13:32,399 --> 00:13:33,759
I'm here to look for Xiaocan.

205
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:37,440
Xiaocan, Xiaocan.

206
00:13:42,039 --> 00:13:43,000
Xiaocan.

207
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:51,120
Xiaocan, you guys...

208
00:13:59,000 --> 00:13:59,679
Coming!

209
00:14:02,799 --> 00:14:03,240
Guifang!

210
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,960
I heard you have a fever, a really bad one.

211
00:14:05,759 --> 00:14:06,840
You can't just take random medicine at home.

212
00:14:06,919 --> 00:14:08,120
Let's go, let's go to the hospital.

213
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:09,600
I just... I just need to rest a bit.

214
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:10,159
Xiaorui, no, no.

215
00:14:10,399 --> 00:14:11,440
The doctor has to say you're okay.

216
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:12,399
Keys, keys.

217
00:14:12,399 --> 00:14:12,919
I'll take the keys.

218
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:13,960
Let's go, let's go.

219
00:14:14,679 --> 00:14:15,600
But... but that...

220
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,240
It's fine, it's fine, let's go.

221
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:18,480
The lights aren't off yet.

222
00:14:19,399 --> 00:14:20,240
Don't look, don't look.

223
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:38,440
Wait a minute

224
00:14:40,039 --> 00:14:41,039
I didn't bring my ID

225
00:14:41,039 --> 00:14:41,759
Just wait for me

226
00:14:42,759 --> 00:14:43,200
Um...

227
00:14:43,519 --> 00:14:45,720
You don't need it. The community clinic is fine

228
00:14:45,720 --> 00:14:47,360
No, I can't go without my ID

229
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:48,240
I can't see a doctor anywhere

230
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:49,200
Wait for me. I'll be right back

231
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:49,799
It'll be quick

232
00:14:56,399 --> 00:14:57,360
Xiaocan, what are you doing?

233
00:14:58,440 --> 00:14:59,720
Why are you robbing your own house?

234
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:03,039
My mom has amnesia

235
00:15:03,639 --> 00:15:04,440
Amnesia?

236
00:15:05,519 --> 00:15:06,440
How did she suddenly get amnesia?

237
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:08,440
My mom couldn't accept that I traded my life for hers

238
00:15:09,039 --> 00:15:09,679
She would grow old

239
00:15:09,840 --> 00:15:10,960
The Life Energy would be useless

240
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,080
I was afraid she'd be too heartbroken

241
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,720
So I signed a supplemental agreement with A Fu

242
00:15:14,159 --> 00:15:15,480
To erase me from her memory

243
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,360
So I have to remove all traces of me

244
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:17,919
Clear them all away

245
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:20,960
Will she be able to remember?

246
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:22,679
Yes

247
00:15:23,279 --> 00:15:24,600
But we absolutely can't let her remember

248
00:15:24,759 --> 00:15:26,240
You too. You must not let her remember me

249
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,240
You have to play along. Do you hear me?

250
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:28,559
Never let her remember me

251
00:15:28,879 --> 00:15:29,279
Guifang

252
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,039
It's okay if you didn't bring your ID

253
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:31,919
It doesn't matter

254
00:15:31,919 --> 00:15:33,000
It really doesn't matter. We can see the doctor

255
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:33,600
Um...

256
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:34,960
Wait, why is this door open?

257
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:36,080
I remember closing it

258
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:39,120
Xiaotian

259
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:45,399
Why are you here?

260
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:47,720
I...

261
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:50,840
I...

262
00:15:57,399 --> 00:16:00,519
So all these things in the house are yours?

263
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:02,600
These things?

264
00:16:07,879 --> 00:16:08,240
Yes

265
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:09,600
They're all mine

266
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:14,639
Then the two of us...

267
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:15,559
Well...

268
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:17,799
Are... are living together?

269
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:19,120
Yeah

270
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:20,600
Living together

271
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:23,080
Living together

272
00:16:26,759 --> 00:16:29,480
The person living with me is Xiaotian

273
00:16:40,559 --> 00:16:41,360
It rained that day

274
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,559
It was feeling sorry for me

275
00:16:42,559 --> 00:16:43,720
It was crying for me

276
00:16:43,919 --> 00:16:44,519
What? Let me tell you

277
00:16:44,519 --> 00:16:45,360
I bought you a gift

278
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:46,519
I bought you a bear

279
00:16:46,519 --> 00:16:47,320
Look how cute it is

280
00:16:47,759 --> 00:16:48,320
A gift for you

281
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,519
Are you crazy?

282
00:16:49,759 --> 00:16:51,279
Where are we supposed to put something this big?

283
00:16:51,679 --> 00:16:53,200
Don't you know how big our place is?

284
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:54,759
After I bought it today, I went to get on the bus...

285
00:16:54,759 --> 00:16:55,639
And they wouldn't let me take it

286
00:16:55,639 --> 00:16:56,720
I had to buy another ticket

287
00:16:58,960 --> 00:16:59,799
Okay, okay. Don't be mad

288
00:16:59,799 --> 00:17:00,440
If you have that money...

289
00:17:00,639 --> 00:17:01,720
You could've bought something useful

290
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:02,120
Let me tell you

291
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:03,440
Even buying me a durian would be better than this

292
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:04,519
Okay, I'll go back and buy you a durian

293
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:09,200
Guifang

294
00:17:10,119 --> 00:17:10,880
This egg...

295
00:17:11,599 --> 00:17:12,160
It's not cooked through

296
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:12,599
What is this?

297
00:17:12,759 --> 00:17:14,079
Why is this all burnt?

298
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:18,960
Like this...

299
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:19,759
It looks good

300
00:17:20,599 --> 00:17:20,920
Like this...

301
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:21,640
It looks good

302
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:24,559
This is really good

303
00:17:29,359 --> 00:17:30,160
Um...

304
00:17:30,319 --> 00:17:31,000
Um...

305
00:17:31,279 --> 00:17:32,799
You have a fever right now

306
00:17:32,799 --> 00:17:34,359
You shouldn't be standing like this

307
00:17:34,359 --> 00:17:35,440
You need to go rest in bed

308
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:36,240
You'll only get better if you rest

309
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:38,440
You can't stand here, it'll get worse

310
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:56,119
What were you thinking?

311
00:17:57,079 --> 00:17:59,000
I-I... I really wasn't thinking straight.

312
00:17:59,160 --> 00:17:59,640
You weren't?

313
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:01,759
Really wasn't.

314
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:03,599
Really?

315
00:18:06,319 --> 00:18:07,400
You should thank him for being there.

316
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:09,759
If he hadn't been there today...

317
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:10,880
...we never could have covered this up.

318
00:18:15,039 --> 00:18:16,160
To avoid agitating Auntie...

319
00:18:17,319 --> 00:18:18,519
...let's just go with what she thinks.

320
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:19,279
You...

321
00:18:19,839 --> 00:18:20,839
...will play her boyfriend.

322
00:18:22,279 --> 00:18:23,519
Is... is that okay?

323
00:18:23,599 --> 00:18:24,240
No.

324
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:24,799
Does it matter?

325
00:18:31,119 --> 00:18:32,240
Guifang's still running a fever.

326
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:33,720
I have to trouble you to take care of her.

327
00:18:35,119 --> 00:18:35,640
And one more thing.

328
00:18:36,359 --> 00:18:39,200
You absolutely cannot let her remember Xiaocan.

329
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:41,880
Or it'll trigger serious side effects.

330
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:43,880
Most importantly...

331
00:18:45,039 --> 00:18:47,480
...what you should and shouldn't do.

332
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:48,880
I trust...

333
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:50,839
...you know your limits.

334
00:18:56,599 --> 00:18:57,559
D-Don't worry.

335
00:18:58,440 --> 00:18:59,160
I know.

336
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:22,079
Why is my head still such a mess?

337
00:19:23,279 --> 00:19:24,440
I feel like I've forgotten something.

338
00:19:47,599 --> 00:19:48,000
Guifang.

339
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:48,839
You're up.

340
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:50,119
How are you?

341
00:19:50,279 --> 00:19:50,799
Feeling any better?

342
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:52,440
Much better.

343
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:55,000
What... what's wrong with your arm?

344
00:19:55,720 --> 00:19:56,799
I was checking your temperature.

345
00:19:58,119 --> 00:19:59,200
You must be hungry. Eat up.

346
00:20:01,119 --> 00:20:01,920
I made a bowl of fish soup.

347
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:03,599
It's very nourishing. Have a taste.

348
00:20:04,920 --> 00:20:06,680
I thought you didn't know how to make fish soup?

349
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:09,119
Does... does Xiaocan not know how to cook fish?

350
00:20:10,319 --> 00:20:10,680
I...

351
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:12,519
I just learned how.

352
00:20:13,599 --> 00:20:14,000
Try it.

353
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:20,839
How is it?

354
00:20:21,039 --> 00:20:21,759
It's pretty good.

355
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:25,160
Don't just stand there. Sit down.

356
00:20:30,559 --> 00:20:31,039
How are you feeling?

357
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:32,279
Still have a fever? Let me check.

358
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:33,200
Not really burning anymore.

359
00:20:34,799 --> 00:20:35,799
Still a little warm.

360
00:20:36,279 --> 00:20:37,599
Get some rest after you finish eating.

361
00:20:38,759 --> 00:20:39,400
You eat too.

362
00:20:40,200 --> 00:20:40,759
Right, right, right.

363
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:58,640
The fever really muddled my head.

364
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:00,839
How could I forget that Xiaotian is my boyfriend?

365
00:21:00,839 --> 00:21:02,000
How could I forget something like that?

366
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:04,200
Xiaotian.

367
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:08,680
There's something I want to confess.

368
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,480
Actually, today I...

369
00:21:11,759 --> 00:21:13,279
I might be confused from the fever...

370
00:21:14,119 --> 00:21:15,799
...but there are a lot of things that I...

371
00:21:16,359 --> 00:21:17,799
...that I don't remember very clearly.

372
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:19,119
Are we...

373
00:21:20,759 --> 00:21:21,680
...a couple?

374
00:21:25,119 --> 00:21:25,559
We...

375
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:28,839
We are a couple.

376
00:21:29,839 --> 00:21:30,640
We're a couple.

377
00:21:37,759 --> 00:21:39,160
Then how did we get together?

378
00:21:45,039 --> 00:21:45,400
You...

379
00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:47,640
You were just...

380
00:21:49,519 --> 00:21:49,799
Just...

381
00:21:50,839 --> 00:21:52,079
...moved by me.

382
00:21:54,279 --> 00:21:54,920
I said...

383
00:21:55,319 --> 00:21:56,920
...I'd always support you in achieving your dreams.

384
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:00,720
Support you in everything you want to do.

385
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:02,839
I'd never get in your way.

386
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:05,640
Just watching over you silently would be enough.

387
00:22:11,240 --> 00:22:12,960
A-And then you... then you agreed.

388
00:22:16,759 --> 00:22:17,279
Is that so?

389
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:19,880
I see.

390
00:22:21,839 --> 00:22:23,039
Will you stay here tonight?

391
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:42,400
No.

392
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:43,480
It was just the angle.

393
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:48,880
You don't trust Wei Mingtian?

394
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:51,359
I'm a little worried about my mom, too.

395
00:22:53,079 --> 00:22:55,160
So what happens now?

396
00:22:55,599 --> 00:22:58,160
Are you really going to let Auntie forget everything?

397
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,279
What else can I do?

398
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:05,160
You can't have everything in this world.

399
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:06,920
Why should I be the one to get it all?

400
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:08,799
I've already been given one incredible miracle.

401
00:23:09,119 --> 00:23:10,279
So I have to pay a price.

402
00:23:11,119 --> 00:23:11,920
This price...

403
00:23:12,799 --> 00:23:14,920
...was determined the day I signed the contract.

404
00:23:24,759 --> 00:23:25,519
But I don't regret it.

405
00:23:31,480 --> 00:23:32,759
We really are...

406
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:34,039
...being a bit creepy right now.

407
00:23:34,240 --> 00:23:35,160
But it's also kind of romantic.

408
00:23:59,359 --> 00:24:00,640
Will you be staying here tonight?

409
00:24:03,519 --> 00:24:03,920
Here.

410
00:24:03,920 --> 00:24:04,920
Guifang, time for your medicine.

411
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:05,480
Thanks.

412
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:06,559
Next question.

413
00:24:06,839 --> 00:24:08,960
Which was China's first hydroelectric station?

414
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:12,480
Do you know the answer he mentioned?

415
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:15,200
The Shilongba Hydropower Station, 1910.

416
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:15,920
Shilongba Hydropower Station.

417
00:24:16,039 --> 00:24:16,759
Correct.

418
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:18,640
Really?

419
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:21,240
You're amazing.

420
00:24:36,279 --> 00:24:38,519
What should be done, what shouldn't be done...

421
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:39,880
...you should know better.

422
00:24:54,480 --> 00:24:55,359
Why are you burning up?

423
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:58,480
Did I pass it to you?

424
00:24:59,680 --> 00:25:01,319
You're sweating so much. Let me see.

425
00:25:04,599 --> 00:25:06,759
What to do, what not to do...

426
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:08,000
What not to do...

427
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:10,599
Shouldn't... shouldn't... shouldn't do what?

428
00:25:12,839 --> 00:25:13,920
I have an event early tomorrow morning.

429
00:25:14,119 --> 00:25:15,160
I told them to pick me up at school.

430
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:16,359
I'll sleep at school tonight.

431
00:25:16,519 --> 00:25:17,119
Get some rest.

432
00:25:25,839 --> 00:25:27,640
Are we really boyfriend and girlfriend?

433
00:25:29,039 --> 00:25:30,519
But why do I always feel...

434
00:25:30,799 --> 00:25:32,319
...that he's acting so awkward?

435
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:34,799
What?

436
00:25:35,279 --> 00:25:36,240
Amnesia?

437
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:39,079
Don't be so dramatic, you two.

438
00:25:40,279 --> 00:25:40,759
Anyway...

439
00:25:41,519 --> 00:25:44,039
...just don't upset Guifang with Xiaocan's situation.

440
00:26:00,319 --> 00:26:01,480
Did my mom...

441
00:26:02,559 --> 00:26:03,440
...really forget me?

442
00:26:03,799 --> 00:26:05,039
She didn't remember anything at all?

443
00:26:06,920 --> 00:26:08,119
She was busy studying again last night.

444
00:26:08,519 --> 00:26:09,240
She forgot everything.

445
00:26:15,720 --> 00:26:16,400
It's good that she forgot.

446
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:18,519
It's good.

447
00:26:23,039 --> 00:26:24,519
Don't forget to remind her to take her meds.

448
00:26:25,559 --> 00:26:26,039
Okay.

449
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:40,559
So...

450
00:26:41,519 --> 00:26:42,720
...Xiaocan will be all alone...

451
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:45,359
...spending his last ten-odd days by himself.

452
00:26:47,319 --> 00:26:48,079
Perhaps...

453
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:50,200
...this is the best way.

454
00:27:08,440 --> 00:27:10,240
I said it's a girls' gathering, but you insisted on coming.

455
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:11,720
Don't you know you're a third wheel?

456
00:27:12,079 --> 00:27:13,440
Aren't I just worried about Godmother?

457
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:17,759
What's wrong, Fang'er?

458
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:21,720
That beef patty place...

459
00:27:22,960 --> 00:27:24,559
I feel like I've eaten there with someone.

460
00:27:28,119 --> 00:27:28,880
With whom?

461
00:27:36,559 --> 00:27:37,519
It was a boy.

462
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:40,119
Was it Wei Mingtian?

463
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:44,440
Me! It was me!

464
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:45,799
That boy was me.

465
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:47,680
Beef patties, right?

466
00:27:48,880 --> 00:27:49,200
Right.

467
00:27:50,079 --> 00:27:50,839
Yes, it was him.

468
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:51,279
Right.

469
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:52,920
Smelling it makes me hungry.

470
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:54,559
Let's go eat that.

471
00:27:54,559 --> 00:27:55,359
It looks delicious.

472
00:27:55,359 --> 00:27:56,599
This is good. This place has a nice atmosphere.

473
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:57,039
Let's go, let's go.

474
00:27:57,400 --> 00:27:58,079
Hurry, let's go.

475
00:27:58,720 --> 00:27:59,279
This place is good.

476
00:27:59,279 --> 00:28:00,000
This place is delicious.

477
00:28:04,039 --> 00:28:04,839
You're setting yourself up.

478
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:10,240
Fang'er, I just thought of something.

479
00:28:10,279 --> 00:28:11,359
That... that place is even better.

480
00:28:11,359 --> 00:28:12,240
Let's go eat at that one.

481
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:13,000
Right, right, right. It's delicious.

482
00:28:13,039 --> 00:28:13,799
That place is especially good.

483
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:14,480
Let's go, let's go.

484
00:28:14,480 --> 00:28:14,920
Look, look.

485
00:28:15,079 --> 00:28:15,440
Let's go. It's tasty.

486
00:28:19,759 --> 00:28:20,200
Xu Rui.

487
00:28:20,319 --> 00:28:20,920
No...

488
00:28:20,920 --> 00:28:21,680
Isn't that Xu Rui?

489
00:28:21,799 --> 00:28:22,160
You're mistaken.

490
00:28:22,160 --> 00:28:22,599
I don't think so.

491
00:28:22,599 --> 00:28:23,440
It looks just like her. Let me take a good look.

492
00:28:25,640 --> 00:28:26,279
What's going on?

493
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:26,960
Xu Rui!

494
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:29,000
It really is her.

495
00:28:29,319 --> 00:28:30,079
Talk about a coincidence.

496
00:28:30,079 --> 00:28:30,640
What a coincidence.

497
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:31,680
You're eating here too?

498
00:28:36,759 --> 00:28:38,480
And this is...

499
00:28:40,119 --> 00:28:41,960
My boyfriend.

500
00:28:58,799 --> 00:29:00,160
Hello, hello. My name is Kong Guifang.

501
00:29:01,359 --> 00:29:01,720
Hello.

502
00:29:03,319 --> 00:29:04,559
Kong Huoshan.

503
00:29:04,640 --> 00:29:05,119
Kong Huoshan.

504
00:29:05,279 --> 00:29:05,640
Kong Huoshan.

505
00:29:06,079 --> 00:29:06,799
Same surname as me.

506
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:07,640
What a coincidence.

507
00:29:07,759 --> 00:29:08,440
What a coincidence.

508
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:09,960
Let's eat here then.

509
00:29:09,960 --> 00:29:10,839
Xu Rui is here too.

510
00:29:10,839 --> 00:29:11,880
We can order more dishes. Let's not eat that.

511
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:12,440
I think that place is fine too.

512
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:13,079
This looks pretty good.

513
00:29:13,079 --> 00:29:13,759
Is that okay, Xu Rui?

514
00:29:14,839 --> 00:29:15,720
Is it okay? Is it?

515
00:29:16,599 --> 00:29:17,400
Let's just eat here.

516
00:29:27,559 --> 00:29:27,920
Xu Rui.

517
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:30,319
When did you get a boyfriend?

518
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:31,240
How come I didn't know?

519
00:29:31,240 --> 00:29:32,200
You didn't tell me either.

520
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:34,640
We just started dating, not long ago.

521
00:29:37,319 --> 00:29:38,079
Do you two know?

522
00:29:38,359 --> 00:29:38,559
We know.

523
00:29:38,559 --> 00:29:38,880
We don't know.

524
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:39,960
We know.

525
00:29:39,960 --> 00:29:40,279
We don't know.

526
00:29:44,039 --> 00:29:44,960
Do you know or not?

527
00:29:46,240 --> 00:29:47,119
They know.

528
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:49,880
But it's their first time meeting him in person today.

529
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:53,319
Right.

530
00:29:53,880 --> 00:29:55,319
It's our first time meeting today too.

531
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:58,519
Bro, first time meeting.

532
00:29:59,240 --> 00:30:00,799
I often hear Sister Rui mention you.

533
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:02,000
She says you're a really good person.

534
00:30:02,920 --> 00:30:03,799
Meeting you today...

535
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:04,759
I feel like we've known each other...

536
00:30:04,759 --> 00:30:05,640
...for over twenty years.

537
00:30:07,599 --> 00:30:08,000
Hello.

538
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:12,559
So how did you two meet?

539
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:15,160
He kept coming to watch my matches.

540
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:18,000
And brought me food and drinks.

541
00:30:18,079 --> 00:30:18,920
Gave me gifts.

542
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:20,400
Stuck to me like a leech.

543
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:21,480
I couldn't shake him off no matter what.

544
00:30:22,279 --> 00:30:24,160
He treats you really well then.

545
00:30:24,839 --> 00:30:27,279
Look at this young man, he looks quite...

546
00:30:28,480 --> 00:30:29,160
Honest and simple.

547
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:32,839
Look, he keeps eating and doesn't talk much.

548
00:30:33,039 --> 00:30:34,519
Quite... quite introverted.

549
00:30:35,319 --> 00:30:35,839
That's good.

550
00:30:36,799 --> 00:30:37,400
Reliable.

551
00:30:40,319 --> 00:30:42,119
Why aren't you two eating? Come on.

552
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:44,000
Doesn't Xiaoyin like these fried dough sticks?

553
00:30:44,039 --> 00:30:44,559
Meatballs.

554
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:45,640
Help yourself. You put it in for her.

555
00:30:45,960 --> 00:30:46,519
Help yourself, help yourself.

556
00:30:46,599 --> 00:30:47,200
Seriously.

557
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:49,799
Who likes pork liver?

558
00:30:50,920 --> 00:30:51,759
Which of you two likes it?

559
00:30:52,240 --> 00:30:53,200
Me? I don't eat it.

560
00:30:53,400 --> 00:30:54,160
Xu Rui, you like it.

561
00:30:56,799 --> 00:30:57,880
I don't like pork liver either.

562
00:30:57,880 --> 00:30:58,720
Why did I take this?

563
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:09,440
Forget it, let's just leave it.

564
00:31:13,039 --> 00:31:14,559
You like it.

565
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:20,839
You two are too slow putting the food in.

566
00:31:20,839 --> 00:31:21,359
Hurry up.

567
00:31:21,759 --> 00:31:22,359
Put it in, quick.

568
00:31:22,359 --> 00:31:23,440
Don't you love these meatballs?

569
00:31:23,559 --> 00:31:24,039
Come on, come on.

570
00:31:24,039 --> 00:31:24,759
I'll do it myself, I'll do it.

571
